---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'Two Queries';
const subtitle = 'Same intent, two query formats. Watch the ranking diverge.';
---
<Base title={title} description={subtitle}>
  <article class="etude">
    <p class="essay-kicker">Etude · Know Thyself, Part II</p>
    <h1>Same intent. Two queries. Watch the ranking change.</h1>
    <p class="essay-sub">{subtitle}</p>
    <div class="essay-meta">
      <a href="/essays/know-thyself-search/">← back to essay</a>
    </div>
    <hr />

    <p>A human types <em>"LLM evaluation"</em> into a search box. An agent sends a long declarative query — a sentence describing the shape of the answer it wants. Same intent. Different query format. Different optimal index.</p>

    <div class="queries">
      <label class="qcol">
        <span class="qlabel">Human-style keyword query</span>
        <input id="q-human" type="text" placeholder="LLM evaluation" />
      </label>
      <label class="qcol">
        <span class="qlabel">Agent-style declarative query</span>
        <input id="q-agent" type="text" placeholder="Here is a great article about evaluating LLM outputs against benchmark suites:" />
      </label>
    </div>

    <div class="run">
      <button type="button" id="run-search">Search both</button>
    </div>

    <div id="results" class="results" aria-live="polite"></div>

    <hr />

    <p>Bryk's three axes: query complexity, result volume, ranking semantics. Humans want ten links. Agents want every match. Type like a human, then like an agent — same intent, different optimal index. The substrate underneath has to know which kind of reader is at the other end.</p>
  </article>
</Base>

<script is:inline>
  // Toy index: 8 docs about LLM evaluation.
  // tfidf = how often the verbatim phrase "LLM evaluation" lands in the doc.
  // embed = mocked embedding similarity to a declarative description of
  //         "what a thoughtful answer about evaluating LLM outputs looks like".
  const docs = [
    { id: 'd1', title: '17 LLM Evaluation Tools You Need in 2025', snippet: 'A listicle. "LLM evaluation" appears 41 times. Mostly affiliate links and screenshots.', tfidf: 0.97, embed: 0.18 },
    { id: 'd2', title: 'Holistic Evaluation of Language Models (HELM)', snippet: 'Stanford preprint. Multi-metric framework across accuracy, calibration, robustness, fairness.', tfidf: 0.42, embed: 0.94 },
    { id: 'd3', title: 'Why Most LLM Benchmarks Mislead — and What to Do Instead', snippet: 'Long-form essay. Argues benchmarks measure proxies; proposes task-anchored evals.', tfidf: 0.51, embed: 0.91 },
    { id: 'd4', title: 'How [Vendor] Cut LLM Evaluation Costs by 73%', snippet: 'Vendor blog. "LLM evaluation" in every paragraph. Conclusion: buy our platform.', tfidf: 0.93, embed: 0.22 },
    { id: 'd5', title: 'The Eval Newsletter — Issue #44', snippet: 'Roundup of recent evaluation papers and toolkits. Light commentary, dense links.', tfidf: 0.66, embed: 0.49 },
    { id: 'd6', title: 'Beyond Pass@1: Measuring Reasoning in Code Models', snippet: 'NeurIPS paper. Introduces a new benchmark suite for multi-step coding evaluation.', tfidf: 0.34, embed: 0.88 },
    { id: 'd7', title: 'A Beginner Tutorial: Evaluating Your First LLM', snippet: 'Tutorial. Walks through running an eval harness against a small model end to end.', tfidf: 0.78, embed: 0.55 },
    { id: 'd8', title: 'Fireside Chat: How We Evaluate Frontier Models (transcript)', snippet: 'Transcript of a conference panel. Discursive, anecdotal, occasional concrete metric.', tfidf: 0.29, embed: 0.71 }
  ];

  function rank(by) {
    return [...docs].sort((a, b) => b[by] - a[by]).map((d, i) => ({ ...d, rank: i + 1 }));
  }

  function badge(humanRank, agentRank, side) {
    const diff = side === 'human' ? agentRank - humanRank : humanRank - agentRank;
    // For each side, show how this doc's rank shifted vs the other column.
    const myRank = side === 'human' ? humanRank : agentRank;
    const otherRank = side === 'human' ? agentRank : humanRank;
    if (myRank <= 3 && otherRank >= 6) return '<span class="badge up">↑↑</span>';
    if (myRank >= 6 && otherRank <= 3) return '<span class="badge down">↓↓</span>';
    return '';
  }

  function renderColumn(list, otherList, side) {
    return list.map(doc => {
      const other = otherList.find(o => o.id === doc.id);
      return `<li data-id="${doc.id}" data-rank="${doc.rank}" data-other="${other.rank}">
        <span class="rk">${doc.rank}.</span>
        <span class="ttl">${doc.title}</span>
        ${badge(side === 'human' ? doc.rank : other.rank, side === 'human' ? other.rank : doc.rank, side)}
        <div class="snip">${doc.snippet}</div>
      </li>`;
    }).join('');
  }

  function drawLines(humanList, agentList) {
    const svg = document.getElementById('shift-svg');
    if (!svg) return;
    svg.innerHTML = '';
    const container = document.getElementById('results-grid');
    const cRect = container.getBoundingClientRect();
    svg.setAttribute('width', cRect.width);
    svg.setAttribute('height', cRect.height);
    humanList.forEach(doc => {
      const leftEl = container.querySelector(`.col-human li[data-id="${doc.id}"]`);
      const rightEl = container.querySelector(`.col-agent li[data-id="${doc.id}"]`);
      if (!leftEl || !rightEl) return;
      const lr = leftEl.getBoundingClientRect();
      const rr = rightEl.getBoundingClientRect();
      const x1 = lr.right - cRect.left;
      const y1 = lr.top + lr.height / 2 - cRect.top;
      const x2 = rr.left - cRect.left;
      const y2 = rr.top + rr.height / 2 - cRect.top;
      const dy = Math.abs(y2 - y1);
      const moved = dy > 4;
      const line = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'line');
      line.setAttribute('x1', x1);
      line.setAttribute('y1', y1);
      line.setAttribute('x2', x2);
      line.setAttribute('y2', y2);
      line.setAttribute('stroke', moved ? 'rgba(138,52,32,0.55)' : 'rgba(0,0,0,0.12)');
      line.setAttribute('stroke-width', moved ? '1.5' : '1');
      line.setAttribute('stroke-dasharray', moved ? '0' : '3 3');
      svg.appendChild(line);
    });
  }

  function runSearch() {
    const humanList = rank('tfidf');
    const agentList = rank('embed');
    const html = `
      <div id="results-grid" class="results-grid">
        <svg id="shift-svg" class="shift-svg"></svg>
        <div class="col col-human">
          <h3>Keyword query · ranked by tf-idf</h3>
          <ol>${renderColumn(humanList, agentList, 'human')}</ol>
        </div>
        <div class="col col-agent">
          <h3>Declarative query · ranked by embedding similarity</h3>
          <ol>${renderColumn(agentList, humanList, 'agent')}</ol>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="legend">Solid line: rank changed across columns. Dashed line: rank held. <strong>↑↑</strong> jumped into a top-3 from a bottom-3. <strong>↓↓</strong> fell out of a top-3 into a bottom-3.</p>
    `;
    const out = document.getElementById('results');
    out.innerHTML = html;
    requestAnimationFrame(() => {
      // small stagger so the columns feel like they race in
      const lis = out.querySelectorAll('li');
      lis.forEach((li, i) => {
        li.style.animationDelay = (i * 35) + 'ms';
        li.classList.add('in');
      });
      setTimeout(() => drawLines(humanList, agentList), 400);
    });
  }

  document.getElementById('run-search').addEventListener('click', runSearch);
  window.addEventListener('resize', () => {
    if (document.getElementById('results-grid')) {
      drawLines(rank('tfidf'), rank('embed'));
    }
  });
</script>

<style>
  .etude { max-width: 52rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.25rem 4rem; }
  .etude h1 { font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 1.85rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem; line-height: 1.2; }
  .essay-sub { font-style: italic; color: var(--muted); margin: 0 0 1rem; }

  .queries {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .qcol { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.35rem; }
  .qlabel { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); }
  .queries input {
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.7rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.18);
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .queries input:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--accent); }

  .run { margin: 0.5rem 0 1.25rem; }
  #run-search {
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    padding: 0.55rem 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
    border-radius: 3px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 100ms;
  }
  #run-search:hover { background: rgba(138, 52, 32, 0.08); }

  .results { margin: 1rem 0; min-height: 2rem; }
  .results-grid {
    position: relative;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2.25rem;
  }
  .shift-svg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }
  .col { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .col h3 {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    font-weight: normal;
  }
  .col ol {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .col li {
    padding: 0.55rem 0.7rem;
    margin: 0.35rem 0;
    background: var(--bg-soft, rgba(0,0,0,0.03));
    border-radius: 3px;
    line-height: 1.4;
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(4px);
  }
  .col li.in {
    animation: slidein 320ms cubic-bezier(.2,.8,.2,1) forwards;
  }
  @keyframes slidein {
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }
  .col .rk { font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; color: var(--muted); margin-right: 0.4rem; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .col .ttl { font-weight: 500; }
  .col .snip { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 0.2rem; line-height: 1.45; }

  .badge {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-left: 0.4rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    padding: 0.05rem 0.35rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .badge.up { color: #1a6b3a; background: rgba(26,107,58,0.12); }
  .badge.down { color: #8a3420; background: rgba(138,52,32,0.12); }

  .legend {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .queries, .results-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .shift-svg { display: none; }
  }
</style>
